## Domain-Driven Design

### Entities

Domain entities are plain Python dataclasses or Pydantic BaseModel subclasses. They must be **framework-agnostic** — no SQLAlchemy, no FastAPI, no HTTP.

```python
# app/domain/models/dataset.py
from dataclasses import dataclass
from datetime import datetime


@dataclass
class Dataset:
    id: str
    title: str
    category: str
    zone: str
    record_count: int
    price_usd: float
    created_at: datetime
```

Use classes with behavior when the entity has invariants to enforce:

```python
@dataclass
class Dataset:
    id: str
    title: str
    price_usd: float

    def __post_init__(self) -> None:
        if self.price_usd < 0:
            raise ValueError("price_usd must be non-negative")
        if not self.title.strip():
            raise ValueError("title is required")
```

### Repository Interfaces

Define repository contracts in the **domain layer**. Infrastructure implements them.

```python
# app/domain/repositories/i_dataset_repository.py
from abc import ABC, abstractmethod
from app.domain.models.dataset import Dataset


class IDatasetRepository(ABC):
    @abstractmethod
    async def save(self, dataset: Dataset) -> None: ...

    @abstractmethod
    async def find_by_id(self, dataset_id: str) -> Dataset | None: ...

    @abstractmethod
    async def find_all(self, category: str | None = None, zone: str | None = None) -> list[Dataset]: ...
```

### Value Objects

```python
# app/domain/models/value_objects.py
import re
from dataclasses import dataclass


@dataclass(frozen=True)
class Email:
    value: str

    def __post_init__(self) -> None:
        normalized = self.value.strip().lower()
        if not re.match(r"^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$", normalized):
            raise ValueError("Invalid email address")
        object.__setattr__(self, "value", normalized)
```

