## Python Standards

- Python 3.12+ syntax (use `str | None` instead of `Optional[str]`)
- `mypy --strict` must pass with zero errors
- `ruff` for linting and formatting (replaces black + flake8 + isort)
- No `Any` — use `object` or proper generics
- All function signatures must have type annotations (parameters + return type)
- Use `dataclasses.dataclass` for domain entities, Pydantic for I/O schemas
- Prefer `async def` throughout — no blocking I/O in async context
- Constants use `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`, everything else `snake_case`

---

## Git Workflow

- Branch naming: `feature/<ticket-id>-short-description`, `fix/<ticket-id>-short-description`
- Commit message format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>` (Conventional Commits)
  - Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`
  - Example: `feat(datasets): add GET /datasets endpoint`
- One feature per branch, small focused commits
- Always update `openspec/specs/api-spec.yml` when endpoints change
- Always update `openspec/specs/data-model.md` when the database schema changes
